arts.sum: Neil Harris says it’s too soon to determine the full extent of injuries suffered by Josh Coburn and Jake Cooper in the 1-0 loss to Luton Town. “Him and Jake look like calf [injuries].

arts.ttl: The lowdown on Millwall 0-1 Luton - Lions down to one senior striker after Josh Coburn injury blow
arts.sum: Millwall : Jensen, Leonard, Tanganga, Cooper (Hutchinson, 46), Bryan (Scanlon, 79), De Norre, Saville, Esse (Emakhu, 79), Honeyman (Azeez, 67), Watmore, Coburn (Langstaff, 34). Substitute Macaulay Langstaff missed a golden opportunity to equalise for Millwall in the second half when he was put through one-on-one but couldn’t beat Thomas Kaminski, who also denied Shaun Hutchinson from a corner right at the death.

arts.ttl: Luton seal first win of season at Millwall
arts.sum: Teden Mengi's superb finish at The Den gave Luton a much-needed first win of the season as they edged past Millwall 1-0 in the Sky Bet Championship.
